                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1737">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/212.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Demonstration resulting from Costa Rican boundary decision of Justice White,
                    which parties and newspaper opposed to Porras administration <pb facs="1110"
                        n="994" xml:id="pg_994"/> began inciting yesterday, took place tonight;
                    seemingly unsuccessful. Crowd visited presidential mansion and Costa Rican
                    consulate; dispersed by police. Panaman President accused of lack of attention
                    and capability in handling case. American Legation not visited. National
                    Assembly is being called upon to demand reopening of the case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
